section.t:
This document is organized as follows: 
         
            provides the terminology; 
         
         
            provides an overview
           of SPPP, including the functional entities and data model; 
         
            specifies requirements for
           SPPP transport protocols; 
         
            describes the base protocol 
           data structures, the generic response codes and messages, 
           and the basic object type most first class objects extend from;
         
            detailed descriptoins of 
           the data model object specifications;
         
            defines XML
           considerations that XML parsers must meet to conform to
           this specification;  
           normatively defines the SPPP 
          protocol using its XML Schema Definition.
